    "description": "If you're a passionate Reservation Manager with drive and ambition, Sarovar Hotels in Navi Mumbai is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Sarovar Hotels:\nSarovar Hotels is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Manage reservations and optimize room revenue through yield management\n• Conduct regular guest satisfaction surveys and implement improvements\n• Train and supervise front-line staff on service standards\n• Ensure compliance with FSSAI, health, and safety regulations\n• Coordinate housekeeping and maintenance for room readiness\n• Manage procurement of hotel supplies and control operating costs\n• Manage front office operations including check-in/check-out\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Housekeeping Standards\n• Proficiency in Yield Management\n• Proficiency in HACCP\n• Proficiency in Revenue Management\n• Proficiency in GDS Systems\n• Proficiency in Food Safety\n• Proficiency in Customer Relations\n• Proficiency in F&B Service\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Sarovar Hotels!",
